hh3cHgmp.name: hh3cHgmp
hh3cHgmp.contactinfo: Platform Team Hangzhou H3C Tech. Co., Ltd. Hai-Dian District Beijing P.R. China http://www.h3c.com Zip:100085
hh3cHgmp.description: This MIB contains objects to manage the hh3chgmp operations, which are used on lanswitch products.

hh3cClusterObject.name: hh3cClusterObject
hh3cClusterObject.description: This MIB contains objects to manage the cluster operations, which are used on lanswitch products.

hh3chgmpSetVLANSecurity.name: hh3chgmpSetVLANSecurity
hh3chgmpSetVLANSecurity.description: Configure whether to perform the VLAN check inside the cluster.

hh3chgmpHandShakeInterval.name: hh3chgmpHandShakeInterval
hh3chgmpHandShakeInterval.description: Handshaking interval of the cluster member switches.

hh3chgmpHandShakeHoldtime.name: hh3chgmpHandShakeHoldtime
hh3chgmpHandShakeHoldtime.description: Holdtime of administrator switch and member switch in the cluster.

hh3chgmpGrpMemberTableChange.name: hh3chgmpGrpMemberTableChange
hh3chgmpGrpMemberTableChange.description: Add 1 to the member list after it changes. The administrator checks if the value has changed. If not, he will not read the list once more.

hh3chgmpMemberDisconRate.name: hh3chgmpMemberDisconRate
hh3chgmpMemberDisconRate.description: Disconnection times of the member and administrator switches divided by member number times 1000.

hh3chgmpCmdClusterName.name: hh3chgmpCmdClusterName
hh3chgmpCmdClusterName.description: Cluster name of the administrator switch

hh3chgmpMngPriIpSegCMIP.name: hh3chgmpMngPriIpSegCMIP
hh3chgmpMngPriIpSegCMIP.description: The private management IP address of the administrator switch, which can not be modified after the cluster has been created.

hh3chgmpMngPriIpMask.name: hh3chgmpMngPriIpMask
hh3chgmpMngPriIpMask.description: The private management IP address mask assigned by the administrator switch, which cannot be modified after the cluster has been created.

hh3chgmpFtpServer.name: hh3chgmpFtpServer
hh3chgmpFtpServer.description: The cluster members can access the Ftp Server through the administrator switch, which can only be configured and accessed on the administrator switch.

hh3chgmpTftpServer.name: hh3chgmpTftpServer
hh3chgmpTftpServer.description: The cluster members can access the Tftp Server through the administrator switch, which can only be configured and accessed on the administrator switch.

hh3chgmpSnmpHost.name: hh3chgmpSnmpHost
hh3chgmpSnmpHost.description: The Snmp Host to send the cluster trap packets, which can only be configured and accessed on the administrator switch.

hh3chgmpLogHost.name: hh3chgmpLogHost
hh3chgmpLogHost.description: Log host of the cluster, which can only be configured and accessed on the administrator switch.

hh3chgmpGrpMemberDeviceId.name: hh3chgmpGrpMemberDeviceId
hh3chgmpGrpMemberDeviceId.description: 4 bytes reserved as 0x0 + 6 bytes of MAC address, expressed as a character string of the hexadecimal number.

hh3chgmpGrpMemberSerial.name: hh3chgmpGrpMemberSerial
hh3chgmpGrpMemberSerial.description: When adding member switch to the cluster, the administrator switch will assign an unique integer to identify it.

hh3chgmpGrpMemberIpAddr.name: hh3chgmpGrpMemberIpAddr
hh3chgmpGrpMemberIpAddr.description: The private IP addresses of the member switches for the communication inside the cluster.

hh3chgmpGrpMemberPassword.name: hh3chgmpGrpMemberPassword
hh3chgmpGrpMemberPassword.description: Member password for joining a cluster

hh3chgmpGrpMemberPlatform.name: hh3chgmpGrpMemberPlatform
hh3chgmpGrpMemberPlatform.description: Set the hardware platform. A null string indicates the information does not exist in the device adjacency table.

hh3chgmpGrpMemberStatus.name: hh3chgmpGrpMemberStatus
hh3chgmpGrpMemberStatus.description: Member status on the administrator switch, use for displaying the network management status.

hh3chgmpGrpMemberDisconCount.name: hh3chgmpGrpMemberDisconCount
hh3chgmpGrpMemberDisconCount.description: Count of inside communication disconnection between the member switch and the administrator switch.

hh3chgmpGrpMemberEnrollTime.name: hh3chgmpGrpMemberEnrollTime
hh3chgmpGrpMemberEnrollTime.description: Enrollment time of the member, measured in seconds.

hh3chgmpGrpMemberOperate.name: hh3chgmpGrpMemberOperate
hh3chgmpGrpMemberOperate.description: Operation indication field, indicates the operation of adding/removing a member by the network management agent.

hh3chgmpMemberResetTable.name: hh3chgmpMemberResetTable
hh3chgmpMemberResetTable.description: Reset a member switch in the cluster.

hh3chgmpMemberResetMAC.name: hh3chgmpMemberResetMAC
hh3chgmpMemberResetMAC.description: The management MAC address of the switch to be reset, which is the unique identifier of the switch.

hh3chgmpMemberEraseflash.name: hh3chgmpMemberEraseflash
hh3chgmpMemberEraseflash.description: Whether to erase the configuration file from the flash after resetting the switch. Read this node, cannotget(65535) will be returned.

hh3chgmpMemberfailure.name: hh3chgmpMemberfailure
hh3chgmpMemberfailure.description: When a cluster member failure, send a snmp trap to the network management.

hh3chgmpMemberRecover.name: hh3chgmpMemberRecover
hh3chgmpMemberRecover.description: When a cluster member recover, send a snmp trap to the network management.

hh3chgmpMemberStatusChange.name: hh3chgmpMemberStatusChange
hh3chgmpMemberStatusChange.description: When a cluster member status change, send a snmp trap to the network management.

hh3chgmpNetTopChange.name: hh3chgmpNetTopChange
hh3chgmpNetTopChange.description: When net topology of this cluster change, send a snmp trap to the network management.

hh3chgmpClusterMaxPoolNum.name: hh3chgmpClusterMaxPoolNum
hh3chgmpClusterMaxPoolNum.description: Max switch members that the cluster can support(include administrator switch).

hh3chgmpClusterCmdSwMac.name: hh3chgmpClusterCmdSwMac
hh3chgmpClusterCmdSwMac.description: The MAC address of administrator switch. It will be filled with zero when not be a member of cluster.

hh3chgmpClusterProtocolMac.name: hh3chgmpClusterProtocolMac
hh3chgmpClusterProtocolMac.description: Protocol MAC of HGMP protocol family. All multicast packets of this protocol family use this MAC as destination MAC.

hh3chgmpWhitelistTable.name: hh3chgmpWhitelistTable
hh3chgmpWhitelistTable.description: Cluster switches white list table. White list topology is the topology which has been affirmed by network administrator in a cluster, and all devices in white list topology are recorded in this table. Against to white list table, black list table records the devices which are denied to join in cluster. Adding a black list device to white list table will cause a failure.

hh3chgmpWhitelistDeviceId.name: hh3chgmpWhitelistDeviceId
hh3chgmpWhitelistDeviceId.description: Unique identifier indicating a white list switch. Value format of the this object is 'XXXXYYYYYY', in which 'XXXX' is reserved as 4 bytes of 0x0, 'YYYYYY' is a MAC address. For example, if the MAC is 000f-e459-000a, the value of this object is an octet string: '00' '00' '00' '00' '00' '0f' 'e4' '59' '00' '0a'.

hh3chgmpWhitelistSerial.name: hh3chgmpWhitelistSerial
hh3chgmpWhitelistSerial.description: When adding member switch to the cluster, the administrator switch will assign an unique integer to identify it. 0xffff means invalid value for this object.

hh3chgmpWhitelistRowStatus.name: hh3chgmpWhitelistRowStatus
hh3chgmpWhitelistRowStatus.description: The row status of this table.

hh3chgmpWhitelistNbTable.name: hh3chgmpWhitelistNbTable
hh3chgmpWhitelistNbTable.description: Cluster switches white list neighboring information table. White list neighbor table records all neighbor devices for every white list device. In fact, white list neighbor table displays the whole white list topology.

hh3chgmpWhitelistNbIndex.name: hh3chgmpWhitelistNbIndex
hh3chgmpWhitelistNbIndex.description: Index of a switch which is the neighbor of a white list switch identified by 'hgmpWhitelistDeviceId'.

hh3chgmpWhitelistNbDeviceId.name: hh3chgmpWhitelistNbDeviceId
hh3chgmpWhitelistNbDeviceId.description: Unique identifier indicating a neighbor switch of a white list switch. Value format of the this object is 'XXXXYYYYYY', in which 'XXXX' is reserved as 4 bytes of 0x0, 'YYYYYY' is a MAC address. For example, if the MAC is 000f-e459-000a, the value of this object is an octet string: '00' '00' '00' '00' '00' '0f' 'e4' '59' '00' '0a'.

hh3chgmpWhitelistPortName.name: hh3chgmpWhitelistPortName
hh3chgmpWhitelistPortName.description: The name of the port which a white list switch connects to the neighbor specified by 'hgmpWhitelistNbIndex'.

hh3chgmpWhitelistNbPortName.name: hh3chgmpWhitelistNbPortName
hh3chgmpWhitelistNbPortName.description: The name of the port which a neighbor device connects to the white list switch specified by 'hgmpWhitelistDeviceId'.

hh3chgmpBlacklistTable.name: hh3chgmpBlacklistTable
hh3chgmpBlacklistTable.description: Cluster switches black list table. The black list table records all black list devices, and a device in black list is not permitted to join in any cluster.

hh3chgmpBlacklistDeviceId.name: hh3chgmpBlacklistDeviceId
hh3chgmpBlacklistDeviceId.description: Unique identifier indicating a black list switch. Value format of the this object is 'XXXXYYYYYY', in which 'XXXX' is reserved as 4 bytes of 0x0, 'YYYYYY' is a MAC address. For example, if the MAC is 000f-e459-000a, the value of this object is an octet string: '00' '00' '00' '00' '00' '0f' 'e4' '59' '00' '0a'.

hh3chgmpBlacklistAccessDeviceId.name: hh3chgmpBlacklistAccessDeviceId
hh3chgmpBlacklistAccessDeviceId.description: Unique identifier indicating the access device of a black list switch. Tracing from a black list device to the cluster commander switch, the device which the black list switch directly connects to is the access device. Value format of the this object is 'XXXXYYYYYY', in which 'XXXX' is reserved as 4 bytes of 0x0, 'YYYYYY' is a MAC address. 10 bytes of 0xff means invalid value for this object. For example, if the MAC is 000f-e459-000a, the value of this object is an octet string: '00' '00' '00' '00' '00' '0f' 'e4' '59' '00' '0a'.

hh3chgmpBlacklistAccessPortName.name: hh3chgmpBlacklistAccessPortName
hh3chgmpBlacklistAccessPortName.description: The port which the access device connecting to the black list switch is named access port, the object returns the access port name. An empty string means invalid value for this object.

hh3chgmpBlacklistRowStatus.name: hh3chgmpBlacklistRowStatus
hh3chgmpBlacklistRowStatus.description: The row status of this table.

hh3chgmpMemberPriPortTable.name: hh3chgmpMemberPriPortTable
hh3chgmpMemberPriPortTable.description: This table contains port number for different network protocols on each member switch. The port number can be used to access a specified member switch with specified protocol and private IP address.

hh3chgmpMemberPriPortEntry.name: hh3chgmpMemberPriPortEntry
hh3chgmpMemberPriPortEntry.description: Information about a specified member private port entry. The indexes of the entry are hh3chgmpGrpMemberDevId and hh3chgmpMemberPriPortProto, which indicate entries in the table.

hh3chgmpMemberDevId.name: hh3chgmpMemberDevId
hh3chgmpMemberDevId.description: Unique identifier indicating the switch in cluster. Value format of the this object is 'XXXXYYYYYY', in which 'XXXX' is is reserved as 4 bytes of 0x0, 'YYYYYY' is a MAC address.

hh3chgmpMemberPriPortProto.name: hh3chgmpMemberPriPortProto
hh3chgmpMemberPriPortProto.description: The index of this table. Each instance value of this object corresponds to a different protocol.

hh3chgmpMemberPriPortProtoDescr.name: hh3chgmpMemberPriPortProtoDescr
hh3chgmpMemberPriPortProtoDescr.description: It describes the hh3chgmpMemberPriPortProtocol object value. For example, it is 'SNMP' when hh3chgmpMemberPriPortProtocol value is 1.

hh3chgmpMemberPriPortNum.name: hh3chgmpMemberPriPortNum
hh3chgmpMemberPriPortNum.description: The private port number of member switch, used by specified hh3chgmpMemberPriPortProto. By using the private IP address, specified protocol and port number, other devices outside cluster can access member switch. The private IP address can be acquired by reading hh3chgmpGrpMemberIpAddr.

hh3cStackObject.name: hh3cStackObject
hh3cStackObject.description: This MIB contains objects to manage the stack operations, which is used on lanswitch products.

hh3chgmpStackMemberTableChange.name: hh3chgmpStackMemberTableChange
hh3chgmpStackMemberTableChange.description: Change identifier of the stack member table.

hh3chgmpStackMemberDisconRate.name: hh3chgmpStackMemberDisconRate
hh3chgmpStackMemberDisconRate.description: Disconnection rate of the stack member switches.

hh3chgmpMainLanswitchFlag.name: hh3chgmpMainLanswitchFlag
hh3chgmpMainLanswitchFlag.description: The status of the local switch in the stack.

hh3chgmpStackIpPoolStartIP.name: hh3chgmpStackIpPoolStartIP
hh3chgmpStackIpPoolStartIP.description: The first address of the management IP network segment assigned by the master switch, which cannot be modified in the case that there is IP address assignment.

hh3chgmpStackIpPoolLength.name: hh3chgmpStackIpPoolLength
hh3chgmpStackIpPoolLength.description: The length of the management IP segment assigned by the master switch, which cannot be modified in the case that there is IP address assignment.

hh3chgmpStackIpPoolMask.name: hh3chgmpStackIpPoolMask
hh3chgmpStackIpPoolMask.description: The mask of the management IP segment assigned by the master switch, which cannot be modified in the case that there is IP address assignment.

hh3chgmpStackMemberDeviceId.name: hh3chgmpStackMemberDeviceId
hh3chgmpStackMemberDeviceId.description: 2 bytes address type of the switch + 2 bytes zero + MAC address, expressed as a hexadecimal number string.

hh3chgmpStackMemberSerial.name: hh3chgmpStackMemberSerial
hh3chgmpStackMemberSerial.description: When adding a member switch to the stack, the master switch will assign an unique integer to identify it.

hh3chgmpStackMemberIpAddr.name: hh3chgmpStackMemberIpAddr
hh3chgmpStackMemberIpAddr.description: The private member IP address for the communication inside the stack.

hh3chgmpStackMemberPassword.name: hh3chgmpStackMemberPassword
hh3chgmpStackMemberPassword.description: Member password for joining a stack.

hh3chgmpStackMemberPlatform.name: hh3chgmpStackMemberPlatform
hh3chgmpStackMemberPlatform.description: Set the hardware platform. A null string indicates the information does not exist in the device adjacency table.

hh3chgmpStackMemberStatus.name: hh3chgmpStackMemberStatus
hh3chgmpStackMemberStatus.description: Member status on the master switch, use for displaying the network management status.

hh3chgmpStackMemberDisconCount.name: hh3chgmpStackMemberDisconCount
hh3chgmpStackMemberDisconCount.description: Count of inside communication disconnection between the member switch and the master switch.

hh3chgmpStackMemberEnrollTime.name: hh3chgmpStackMemberEnrollTime
hh3chgmpStackMemberEnrollTime.description: Enrollment time of the member, measured in seconds.

hh3chgmpStackRole.name: hh3chgmpStackRole
hh3chgmpStackRole.description: This switch's role status in stack.

hh3chgmpStackMaxPoolNum.name: hh3chgmpStackMaxPoolNum
hh3chgmpStackMaxPoolNum.description: Max switch members in one stack that the switch support (include main switch).

hh3chgmpStackMainSwMac.name: hh3chgmpStackMainSwMac
hh3chgmpStackMainSwMac.description: The MAC address of main switch. It will be 00.00.00 when not be a member of stack.

hh3cNDPObject.name: hh3cNDPObject
hh3cNDPObject.description: This MIB contains objects to manage the ndp operations, which are used on lanswitch products.

hh3cNDPHelloTimer.name: hh3cNDPHelloTimer
hh3cNDPHelloTimer.description: NDP packet transmission interval, measured in seconds.

hh3cNDPAgingTime.name: hh3cNDPAgingTime
hh3cNDPAgingTime.description: How long the NDP information of the local switch can be hold in the adjacent switch, measured in seconds.

hh3cNDPChange.name: hh3cNDPChange
hh3cNDPChange.description: Change identifier of the Neighbor table

hh3cNDPPortTable.name: hh3cNDPPortTable
hh3cNDPPortTable.description: Configure to enable/disable the interface NDP of the switch.

hh3cNDPIfIndex.name: hh3cNDPIfIndex
hh3cNDPIfIndex.description: Unique identifier of an interface of the device.

hh3cNDPPortStatus.name: hh3cNDPPortStatus
hh3cNDPPortStatus.description: If it is enable, the device will send and receive the NDP packets via the interface. To disable the NDP function on the interface, set the entry as false.

hh3cNDPPortNbTable.name: hh3cNDPPortNbTable
hh3cNDPPortNbTable.description: NDP neighbor information on the switch.

hh3cNDPPortNbDeviceId.name: hh3cNDPPortNbDeviceId
hh3cNDPPortNbDeviceId.description: 2 bytes address type of the member switch + 2 bytes zero + MAC address, expressed as a character string of the hexadecimal number.

hh3cNDPPortNbPortName.name: hh3cNDPPortNbPortName
hh3cNDPPortNbPortName.description: Unique identifier of a port. A null string indicates that the field was not included in in the latest NDP packet. Interface type + card number / slot number / sequence number.

hh3cNDPPortNbDeviceName.name: hh3cNDPPortNbDeviceName
hh3cNDPPortNbDeviceName.description: Device name. A null string indicates that the field was not included in the latest NDP packet.

hh3cNDPPortNbProductVer.name: hh3cNDPPortNbProductVer
hh3cNDPPortNbProductVer.description: Product version. A null string indicates that the field was not included in the latest NDP packet.

hh3cNDPPortNbHardVer.name: hh3cNDPPortNbHardVer
hh3cNDPPortNbHardVer.description: Hardware version. A null string indicates that the field was not included in the latest NDP packet.

hh3cNDPPortNbBootromVer.name: hh3cNDPPortNbBootromVer
hh3cNDPPortNbBootromVer.description: Bootrom version. A null string indicates that the field was not included in the latest NDP packet.

hh3cNDPPortNbSoftVer.name: hh3cNDPPortNbSoftVer
hh3cNDPPortNbSoftVer.description: Software version. A null string indicates that the field was not included in the latest NDP packet.

hh3cNDPPortNbAgingtime.name: hh3cNDPPortNbAgingtime
hh3cNDPPortNbAgingtime.description: How long the NDP information of the local switch can be hold in the adjacent switch, measured in seconds.

hh3cNTDPObject.name: hh3cNTDPObject
hh3cNTDPObject.description: This MIB contains objects to manage the ntdp operations, which are used on lanswitch products.

hh3chgmpNTDPCollectTopTime.name: hh3chgmpNTDPCollectTopTime
hh3chgmpNTDPCollectTopTime.description: Topology collection interval of the administrator switch of the cluster, measured in minutes.

hh3chgmpNTDPHopRange.name: hh3chgmpNTDPHopRange
hh3chgmpNTDPHopRange.description: Range of the topology collection of the administrator switch

hh3chgmpNTDPRun.name: hh3chgmpNTDPRun
hh3chgmpNTDPRun.description: Enable/Disable the NTDP function on the switch.

hh3chgmpNTDPPortDelay.name: hh3chgmpNTDPPortDelay
hh3chgmpNTDPPortDelay.description: Set the delay to forward the topology request via the ports, measured in milliseconds.

hh3chgmpNTDPHopDelay.name: hh3chgmpNTDPHopDelay
hh3chgmpNTDPHopDelay.description: Set the delay to forward the topology request from every hop, measured in milliseconds.

hh3chgmpNTDPLastTopCollectDuration.name: hh3chgmpNTDPLastTopCollectDuration
hh3chgmpNTDPLastTopCollectDuration.description: Duration of the latest overall topology collection, a performance count measured in seconds.

hh3chgmpNTDPCacheChange.name: hh3chgmpNTDPCacheChange
hh3chgmpNTDPCacheChange.description: Add 1 when the device table changes. The network administrator will check if it has changed before accessing the table. If it has not changed, he will not access again.

hh3chgmpNTDPTOPTableChange.name: hh3chgmpNTDPTOPTableChange
hh3chgmpNTDPTOPTableChange.description: Add 1 when the topology table changes. The network administrator will check if it has changed before accessing the table. If it has not changed, he will not access again.

hh3chgmpNTDPInterfaceTable.name: hh3chgmpNTDPInterfaceTable
hh3chgmpNTDPInterfaceTable.description: Enable/Disable the NTDP on the switch port.

hh3chgmpNTDPInterfaceIfIndex.name: hh3chgmpNTDPInterfaceIfIndex
hh3chgmpNTDPInterfaceIfIndex.description: Unique identifier an interface of the device.

hh3chgmpNTDPInterfaceEnable.name: hh3chgmpNTDPInterfaceEnable
hh3chgmpNTDPInterfaceEnable.description: If it is true, the device will send and receive the NTDP packets via the interface. To disable the NTDP function on the interface, set the entry as false.

hh3chgmpNTDPCacheTable.name: hh3chgmpNTDPCacheTable
hh3chgmpNTDPCacheTable.description: Access the information about the switch from the topology table.

hh3chgmpNTDPCacheHashIndex.name: hh3chgmpNTDPCacheHashIndex
hh3chgmpNTDPCacheHashIndex.description: Our NTDP information is saved in the HASH table on the administrator switch. Using DeviceID as index will lead to the comparison of a large amount of character strings, which puts too many burdens on the administrator switch. A HAHSIndex is added to reduce the character string comparison to the least range.

hh3chgmpNTDPCacheDeviceID.name: hh3chgmpNTDPCacheDeviceID
hh3chgmpNTDPCacheDeviceID.description: 2 bytes address type of the member switch + 2 bytes zero + MAC address, expressed as a character string of the hexadecimal number.

hh3chgmpNTDPCacheClusterName.name: hh3chgmpNTDPCacheClusterName
hh3chgmpNTDPCacheClusterName.description: Name of the cluster including the device.

hh3chgmpNTDPCacheClusterRole.name: hh3chgmpNTDPCacheClusterRole
hh3chgmpNTDPCacheClusterRole.description: Cluster role of the current device, which can be a administrator switch (0x01), member switch(0x02), backup switch(0x03), candidate switch(0x10) or an independent switch (incapable of cluster member) (0x11).

hh3chgmpNTDPCacheCapabilities.name: hh3chgmpNTDPCacheCapabilities
hh3chgmpNTDPCacheCapabilities.description: The capabilities of the device. FF indicates that the field was not included in in the latest NTDP packet.

hh3chgmpNTDPCacheVersion.name: hh3chgmpNTDPCacheVersion
hh3chgmpNTDPCacheVersion.description: The version information of the corresponding device. A null string indicates that the field was not included in in the latest NTDP packet.

hh3chgmpNTDPCachePlatform.name: hh3chgmpNTDPCachePlatform
hh3chgmpNTDPCachePlatform.description: Hardware platform. A null string indicates that the field was not included in the latest NTDP packet.

hh3chgmpNTDPCacheMngVLAN.name: hh3chgmpNTDPCacheMngVLAN
hh3chgmpNTDPCacheMngVLAN.description: The management VLAN ID of the device.

hh3chgmpNTDPTopTable.name: hh3chgmpNTDPTopTable
hh3chgmpNTDPTopTable.description: Access the topology structure collected by the NTDP.

hh3chgmpNTDPTopHashIndex.name: hh3chgmpNTDPTopHashIndex
hh3chgmpNTDPTopHashIndex.description: Our NTDP information is saved in the HASH table on the administrator switch. Using DeviceID as index will lead to the comparison of a large amount of character strings, which puts too many burdens on the administrator switch. A HAHSIndex is added to reduce the character string comparison to the least range.

hh3chgmpNTDPTopEdgeStartDevID.name: hh3chgmpNTDPTopEdgeStartDevID
hh3chgmpNTDPTopEdgeStartDevID.description: 2 bytes address type of the member switch + 2 bytes zero + MAC address, expressed as a character string of the hexadecimal number.

hh3chgmpNTDPTopEdgeIndex.name: hh3chgmpNTDPTopEdgeIndex
hh3chgmpNTDPTopEdgeIndex.description: Edge index of this entry in the data structure.

hh3chgmpNTDPTopEdgeEndDevID.name: hh3chgmpNTDPTopEdgeEndDevID
hh3chgmpNTDPTopEdgeEndDevID.description: 2 bytes address type of the member switch + 2 bytes zero + MAC address, expressed as a character string of the hexadecimal number.

hh3chgmpNTDPTopEdgeStartPort.name: hh3chgmpNTDPTopEdgeStartPort
hh3chgmpNTDPTopEdgeStartPort.description: The number of the first port of a topology edge. Interface type + card number / slot number / sequence number.

hh3chgmpNTDPTopEdgeStartPortFullDuplex.name: hh3chgmpNTDPTopEdgeStartPortFullDuplex
hh3chgmpNTDPTopEdgeStartPortFullDuplex.description: The full-duplex status of the first port on a topology edge.

hh3chgmpNTDPTopEdgeStartPortSpeed.name: hh3chgmpNTDPTopEdgeStartPortSpeed
hh3chgmpNTDPTopEdgeStartPortSpeed.description: The speed of the first port on a topology edge.

hh3chgmpNTDPTopEdgeEndPort.name: hh3chgmpNTDPTopEdgeEndPort
hh3chgmpNTDPTopEdgeEndPort.description: The number of the last port of a topology edge. Interface type + card number / slot number / sequence number.

hh3chgmpNTDPTopLinkStatus.name: hh3chgmpNTDPTopLinkStatus
hh3chgmpNTDPTopLinkStatus.description: In STP or RSTP, it describes link status according to port STP steady status. In MSTP it describes STP steady status of the instance which management VLAN belongs to. Either 'hgmpNTDPTopEdgeStartPort' or 'hgmpNTDPTopEdgeEndPort' STP steady status is 'blocking', this object is 'blocking', otherwise is 'forwarding'. If STP or MSTP is disabled, this object is 'forwarding'.

hh3chgmpStackMemberfailure.name: hh3chgmpStackMemberfailure
hh3chgmpStackMemberfailure.description: When a stack member failure, send a snmp trap to the network management.

hh3chgmpStackMemberRecover.name: hh3chgmpStackMemberRecover
hh3chgmpStackMemberRecover.description: When a stack member Recover, send a snmp trap to the network management.

hh3chgmpStackMemberStatusChange.name: hh3chgmpStackMemberStatusChange
hh3chgmpStackMemberStatusChange.description: When a stack member status change, send a snmp trap to the network management.
